1
00:00:00,033 --> 00:00:03,033
I'm Jake O'Neill creator of animagraphs
我是杰克·奥尼尔动画的创造者
2
00:00:03,133 --> 00:00:06,633
and this is how a World War II submarine works
这就是二战潜艇的工作原理
3
00:00:07,833 --> 00:00:11,100
we've built a generalized teaching model from the era
我们建立了一个通用的教学模式从那个时代开始
4
00:00:11,200 --> 00:00:12,133
for those interested
对于那些感兴趣的人
5
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:12,666
our source
我们的来源
6
00:00:12,666 --> 00:00:16,300
inspiration comes from Gato and Belayo class boats
灵感来自Gato和Belayo级船
7
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:27,200
the submarine consists of a reinforced tube
潜艇由一根加强管组成
8
00:00:27,300 --> 00:00:28,600
called the pressure hole
叫做压力孔
9
00:00:29,000 --> 00:00:31,000
running the length of the ship
运行船的长度
10
00:00:33,466 --> 00:00:36,733
which houses all personnel and sensitive machinery
容纳所有人员和敏感机械
11
00:00:37,700 --> 00:00:38,633
this inner hull
这个内壳
12
00:00:38,633 --> 00:00:40,100
is divided into eight
被分成八个
13
00:00:40,100 --> 00:00:42,466
individually watertight compartments
单独水密隔间
14
00:00:45,033 --> 00:00:48,200
which are separated by reinforced structural barriers
被加固的结构屏障隔开
15
00:00:48,200 --> 00:00:49,433
called bulkheads
称为舱壁
16
00:00:50,400 --> 00:00:53,000
special pressure rated doors separate
特殊额定压力门分开
17
00:00:53,000 --> 00:00:54,800
and isolate these bulkheads
隔离这些舱壁
18
00:00:54,933 --> 00:00:56,266
which we'll examine later
我们稍后会检查。
19
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:02,100
an additional watertight cylinder above the hole
孔上方的附加水密圆柱体
20
00:01:02,100 --> 00:01:03,666
forms the conning tower
形成了指挥塔
21
00:01:07,733 --> 00:01:09,633
wrapped around this core
围绕着这个核心
22
00:01:09,933 --> 00:01:13,266
there's an outer hole which houses tanks for fuel
外面有个洞用来装燃料
23
00:01:13,333 --> 00:01:15,133
ballast water air
压载水空气
24
00:01:15,333 --> 00:01:17,933
and other essential liquids and gases
以及其他必需的液体和气体
25
00:01:19,666 --> 00:01:21,633
a hollow superstructure extends
中空的上层建筑延伸
26
00:01:21,633 --> 00:01:23,200
along the top of the boat
沿着船的顶部
27
00:01:23,333 --> 00:01:24,533
from the main deck
从主甲板
28
00:01:25,133 --> 00:01:28,933
with limber holes so water can flood or drain as needed
带有弹性孔，以便水可以根据需要淹没或排出
29
00:01:35,466 --> 00:01:37,733
now let's get into the details
现在让我们进入细节
30
00:01:37,933 --> 00:01:40,300
starting at the front or bow of the ship
从船的前部或船头开始
31
00:01:41,866 --> 00:01:43,400
there's a large buoyancy tank
有一个大浮箱
32
00:01:43,400 --> 00:01:45,100
that's part of the diving system
那是潜水系统的一部分
33
00:01:47,233 --> 00:01:51,666
shutters on both sides cover six forward torpedo tubes
两边的百叶窗覆盖了六个前鱼雷发射管
34
00:01:54,066 --> 00:01:56,700
the anchor is perched here connected by 600
锚栖息在这里由600连接
35
00:01:56,933 --> 00:01:58,433
feet of chain
链条英尺
36
00:01:59,233 --> 00:02:01,833
the anchor can free fall when released
锚释放时可以自由落体
37
00:02:03,333 --> 00:02:05,833
a motorized device called a wildcat
一种叫做野猫的机动装置
38
00:02:05,866 --> 00:02:07,533
hauls the chain back up
把链条拉回来
39
00:02:08,300 --> 00:02:11,233
storing it in a special chain locker near the bow
存放在船头附近一个特殊的锁链储物柜里
40
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:16,700
the bow planes are also nearby
船头飞机也在附近
41
00:02:18,333 --> 00:02:22,400
a hydraulic ram drives a shaft to tilt the planes
液压柱塞驱动轴使飞机倾斜
42
00:02:22,466 --> 00:02:24,033
allowing the submarine to
允许潜艇
43
00:02:24,033 --> 00:02:26,000
in a way fly through the water
在某种程度上飞过水面
44
00:02:26,000 --> 00:02:27,200
when submerged
淹没时
45
00:02:28,466 --> 00:02:30,666
the planes fold up while surfaced
飞机在浮出水面时折叠起来
46
00:02:30,666 --> 00:02:32,200
since they're no longer needed
因为他们不再需要了
47
00:02:32,466 --> 00:02:34,933
and to protect them from rough seas
保护它们免受汹涌海洋的伤害
48
00:02:39,333 --> 00:02:42,100
from here we can see the forward torpedo room
从这里我们可以看到前方鱼雷室
49
00:02:45,733 --> 00:02:47,866
there are 16 torpedoes here
这里有16枚鱼雷
50
00:02:49,000 --> 00:02:51,666
with six in the tubes ready to fire
管子里有六个准备开火
51
00:02:52,666 --> 00:02:55,300
and 10 reloads stored in the compartment
和10个储存在隔间里的重装
52
00:02:57,033 --> 00:03:00,800
they're 20 plus feet long and 21 inches in diameter
它们长20多英尺直径21英寸
53
00:03:01,133 --> 00:03:03,666
weighing about 3,000 pounds each
每个重约3000磅
54
00:03:05,533 --> 00:03:08,700
between the tubes there's the Gyro Angle Setter
管子之间是陀螺仪角度设置器
55
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:11,533
which continuously updates the angle setting
它不断更新角度设置
56
00:03:11,533 --> 00:03:13,200
inside the torpedoes
在鱼雷里面
57
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:16,133
for firing at a different angle or course
以不同的角度或路线射击
58
00:03:16,133 --> 00:03:17,600
than the submarine itself
而不是潜艇本身
59
00:03:18,033 --> 00:03:19,933
resulting in a curved shot
导致弯曲的镜头
60
00:03:20,700 --> 00:03:23,833
these analog computers are one of many such devices
这些模拟计算机是许多这样的设备之一
61
00:03:23,833 --> 00:03:26,333
on board which we'll examine in more detail
在船上，我们将更详细地检查
62
00:03:26,333 --> 00:03:27,500
as we encounter them
当我们遇到他们时
63
00:03:30,633 --> 00:03:33,200
the torpedoes themselves are expensive
鱼雷本身很贵
64
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,533
technically advanced machines
技术先进的机器
65
00:03:36,866 --> 00:03:40,033
the gyro angle setting from the computer is translated
来自计算机的陀螺仪角度设置被翻译
66
00:03:40,033 --> 00:03:42,300
through a rotating shaft on the tube
通过管子上的转轴
67
00:03:42,400 --> 00:03:44,400
to set the torpedoes inner gyro
设置鱼雷内陀螺仪
68
00:03:45,933 --> 00:03:50,000
rods extend from the gyro rearward to rudder
杆从陀螺仪向后延伸到方向舵
69
00:03:52,066 --> 00:03:54,900
every torpedo has its own adjusted setting
每个鱼雷都有自己的调整设置
70
00:03:54,900 --> 00:03:57,100
based on its location in the submarine
根据它在潜艇里的位置
71
00:03:59,400 --> 00:04:02,066
torpedo depth and speed are set by hand
鱼雷深度和速度由人工设定
72
00:04:02,066 --> 00:04:04,133
from controls on the side of the tube
从管子侧面的控件
73
00:04:04,866 --> 00:04:07,933
the gyro angle can also be set by hand if needed
如果需要，陀螺仪角度也可以手动设置
74
00:04:11,033 --> 00:04:14,233
there are six movable bunks suspended from the ceiling
天花板上悬挂着六个可移动的床铺
75
00:04:14,600 --> 00:04:17,666
but this compartment could accommodate up to 15 beds
但这个隔间最多可容纳15张床
76
00:04:20,433 --> 00:04:22,466
there's a crew's head or toilet here
这里有一个船员的头或厕所
77
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:26,466
and a shower that's mostly used by officers
还有军官常用的淋浴间
78
00:04:28,900 --> 00:04:32,066
a hatch overhead provides access to the escape trunk
头顶的舱门提供了逃生通道
79
00:04:34,266 --> 00:04:36,433
which in turn leads to the bridge
这反过来又通向桥
80
00:04:39,100 --> 00:04:41,466
the escape trunk can be individually sealed
逃生箱可以单独密封
81
00:04:41,466 --> 00:04:43,233
and either flooded or drained
要么被淹没，要么被抽干
82
00:04:44,033 --> 00:04:45,433
flooding may be necessary
洪水可能是必要的
83
00:04:45,433 --> 00:04:48,100
to equalize inside and outside pressure
平衡内外压力
84
00:04:48,200 --> 00:04:51,433
for safe human passage in adverse conditions
在恶劣条件下的安全通行
85
00:04:54,400 --> 00:04:58,033
the underwater log is attached to the port side hole
水下原木附在左舷孔上
86
00:05:02,500 --> 00:05:06,200
with a rod that extends 3 feet beyond the outer hole
用一根延伸到外孔3英尺的棍子
87
00:05:08,033 --> 00:05:10,133
the rod has openings at the tip
杆子尖端有开口
88
00:05:10,200 --> 00:05:11,833
through which seawater flows
海水流经的地方
89
00:05:11,833 --> 00:05:13,500
to measure pressure differences
测量压力差异
90
00:05:15,633 --> 00:05:18,833
and thereby derive speed and distance traveled
从而推导出行驶的速度和距离
91
00:05:24,266 --> 00:05:26,133
heading aft or rearward
向后或向后航行
92
00:05:26,300 --> 00:05:29,233
we pass through a bulkhead with its watertight door
我们穿过有水密门的舱壁
93
00:05:29,933 --> 00:05:32,733
we've now moved into officers quarters
我们现在搬进了军官宿舍
94
00:05:34,500 --> 00:05:35,700
there's a small pantry here
这里有个小储藏室
95
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:37,433
for serving food to officers
为军官提供食物
96
00:05:37,433 --> 00:05:37,666
though
虽然
97
00:05:37,666 --> 00:05:40,600
only coffee and toast are actually prepared here
这里其实只准备了咖啡和吐司
98
00:05:41,300 --> 00:05:43,900
with food itself coming from the cruise galley
食物本身来自游轮厨房
99
00:05:45,666 --> 00:05:49,033
the adjacent officers'wardroom serves as a mess hall
邻近的军官室用作食堂
100
00:05:49,233 --> 00:05:52,200
recreation room workspace and meeting room
娱乐室工作区和会议室
101
00:05:56,933 --> 00:05:59,266
there are four bunks at the other side
另一边有四个铺位
102
00:06:02,400 --> 00:06:05,000
with an additional six bunks down the hall
走廊另加六个床位
103
00:06:08,066 --> 00:06:11,300
the rooms are partitioned with textile curtains
房间用纺织窗帘隔开
104
00:06:13,866 --> 00:06:16,400
the captain's room is separate from the rest
船长的房间和其他房间是分开的
105
00:06:18,300 --> 00:06:21,000
with redundant course indicator and depth gauges
带有冗余的航向指示器和深度计
106
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:22,333
mounted on the wall
挂在墙上
107
00:06:24,533 --> 00:06:25,700
a writing desk
写字台
108
00:06:28,000 --> 00:06:29,466
and wall mounted components
和壁挂式组件
109
00:06:29,466 --> 00:06:32,266
for access to the ship's communication systems
进入飞船的通讯系统
110
00:06:35,233 --> 00:06:35,633
there would be
会有
111
00:06:35,633 --> 00:06:38,100
anywhere from six to eight officers on board
船上有6到8名军官
112
00:06:41,600 --> 00:06:44,266
there's a small office at the end of the hall
大厅尽头有个小办公室
113
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:46,133
with a typewriter for record keeping
用打字机保存记录
114
00:06:51,066 --> 00:06:52,333
from office to country
从办公室到国家
115
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:55,300
we pass through another bulkhead into the control room
我们通过另一个舱壁进入控制室
116
00:06:55,466 --> 00:06:58,400
which is packed to the last square inch
包装到最后一平方英寸
117
00:06:58,433 --> 00:07:00,900
with state of the art technology for its time
拥有当时最先进的技术
118
00:07:04,066 --> 00:07:05,066
at the center
在中心
119
00:07:05,333 --> 00:07:07,100
there's a dead reckoning tracer
有一个死亡推算追踪器
120
00:07:07,466 --> 00:07:09,866
which takes input from the previously shown
它从前面显示的输入中获取输入
121
00:07:09,866 --> 00:07:11,633
underwater log device
水下测井仪
122
00:07:11,800 --> 00:07:13,933
and the nearby master compass
和附近的主指南针
123
00:07:14,266 --> 00:07:16,600
to automatically move a pencil
自动移动铅笔
124
00:07:16,666 --> 00:07:20,000
which draws the ship's course on a map or chart
在地图或海图上画出船的航线
125
00:07:20,000 --> 00:07:20,833
underneath
下面
126
00:07:21,933 --> 00:07:23,900
it has knobs to make adjustments
它有旋钮可以进行调整
127
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:27,600
or recalibrate the device when maps are swapped out
或在更换地图时重新校准设备
128
00:07:29,200 --> 00:07:32,500
the Master Gyrocompass occupies a large case
罗盘大师占据了一个大箱子
129
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:34,266
underneath a central table
在中央桌子下面
130
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:37,133
with a shatterproof glass viewing port
带防碎玻璃观察口
131
00:07:38,333 --> 00:07:41,866
it uses gyroscopic forces to find true north
它利用陀螺力来寻找真正的北方
132
00:07:42,100 --> 00:07:44,033
instead of magnetic north
而不是磁北
133
00:07:45,533 --> 00:07:46,400
magnetic compass
磁罗盘
134
00:07:46,400 --> 00:07:47,000
accuracy
精度
135
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:49,633
can be negatively affected by other electrical
会受到其他电气的负面影响
136
00:07:49,633 --> 00:07:50,833
or metal objects
或金属物体
137
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:52,333
including the ship's hull
包括船体
138
00:07:54,633 --> 00:07:56,533
at the heart of the gyrocompass
在陀螺罗盘的中心
139
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:59,933
a spinning element sits suspended in a cup
一个旋转的元素悬浮在杯子里
140
00:07:59,933 --> 00:08:01,600
partially filled with mercury
部分充满汞
141
00:08:02,400 --> 00:08:05,300
this element's rotation is electrically driven
这个元件的旋转是电动的
142
00:08:06,333 --> 00:08:09,233
the cup is part of a hollow metal sphere
杯子是中空金属球的一部分
143
00:08:09,466 --> 00:08:12,066
that is itself suspended in mercury
它本身悬浮在水银中
144
00:08:13,100 --> 00:08:15,533
encased by an outer supporting sphere
由外支撑球体包裹
145
00:08:17,300 --> 00:08:21,133
the core apparatus is held and isolated from shocks
核心设备被保持并与冲击隔离
146
00:08:21,133 --> 00:08:23,233
by a ring of soft springs
一圈柔软的弹簧
147
00:08:23,233 --> 00:08:25,900
and flexible metal bumpers with felt tips
和带毡尖的柔性金属保险杠
148
00:08:26,733 --> 00:08:29,466
which extend from an inner gimbal ring
从内万向节环延伸
149
00:08:29,933 --> 00:08:32,333
through connection to an outer gimbal ring
通过连接到外部万向节环
150
00:08:32,866 --> 00:08:36,433
the compass maintains its own specific orientation
指南针保持自己特定的方向
151
00:08:36,500 --> 00:08:38,433
apart from the submarine's movement
除了潜艇的移动
152
00:08:39,266 --> 00:08:40,300
the highly sensitive
高度敏感
153
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:41,033
spinning core
纺丝芯
154
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:43,800
maintains its relationship to Earth's gravity
维持它与地球引力的关系
155
00:08:44,100 --> 00:08:45,100
allowing finite
允许有限
156
00:08:45,100 --> 00:08:47,866
directional changes to be continuously tracked
持续跟踪方向变化
157
00:08:50,933 --> 00:08:54,233
above this central table there's a bathy thermograph
在这张中央桌子的上方有一个恒温仪。
158
00:08:54,700 --> 00:08:57,800
that charts water temperature at various depths
绘制不同深度的水温
159
00:08:57,800 --> 00:08:59,100
on paper cards
在纸质卡片上
160
00:08:59,833 --> 00:09:01,066
water temperature affects
水温影响
161
00:09:01,066 --> 00:09:04,300
among other things sonar range and accuracy
声纳的范围和精度
162
00:09:05,133 --> 00:09:08,533
including avoiding sonar detection from other vessels
包括避免其他船只的声纳探测
163
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:10,866
there's a fathometer
有一个测深仪
164
00:09:10,933 --> 00:09:12,800
which displays the result of pings
显示ping的结果
165
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:15,266
to determine the depth of water below the keel
来确定龙骨下面的水深
166
00:09:17,233 --> 00:09:20,733
there are repeating gauges for target bearing and range
目标方位和射程有重复的仪表
167
00:09:24,066 --> 00:09:25,400
along the port side wall
沿左舷壁
168
00:09:25,400 --> 00:09:27,066
which would be the left side of the submarine
也就是潜艇的左侧
169
00:09:27,066 --> 00:09:28,433
looking towards the front
朝前看
170
00:09:28,733 --> 00:09:30,200
there's the diving station
那是潜水站
171
00:09:31,266 --> 00:09:32,300
with separate wheels
有单独的轮子
172
00:09:32,300 --> 00:09:34,133
to control the previously shown bow
控制前面显示的弓
173
00:09:34,133 --> 00:09:35,333
plane angle
平面角
174
00:09:36,033 --> 00:09:38,400
and a similar plane at the stern
船尾还有一架类似的飞机
175
00:09:39,233 --> 00:09:42,400
each wheel has its own water depth to keel gauge
每个轮子都有自己的水深到龙骨量规
176
00:09:43,133 --> 00:09:44,700
plane angle indicator
平面角度指示器
177
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,533
an inclinometer
测斜仪
178
00:09:46,533 --> 00:09:48,933
that works something like a construction level
这就像一个建筑水平
179
00:09:48,933 --> 00:09:50,800
using an air bubble in a liquid
利用液体中的气泡
180
00:09:50,800 --> 00:09:52,133
to track boat angle
跟踪船角度
181
00:09:53,500 --> 00:09:55,300
with separate glass tubes
带有单独的玻璃管
182
00:09:55,733 --> 00:09:57,800
for coarse and fine readings
用于粗略和精细读数
183
00:09:58,666 --> 00:10:01,500
in the center there's a deep depth gauge
在中心有一个深度测量仪
184
00:10:02,200 --> 00:10:05,033
and a barometer to measure internal air pressure
和一个气压计来测量内部气压
185
00:10:07,066 --> 00:10:07,833
moving forward
前进
186
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:11,200
on this side there's the whole opening indicator panel
在这边有整个打开指示器面板
187
00:10:11,833 --> 00:10:12,900
with status lights
