00:28:58,400 --> 00:29:00,666
without excessive help from the planes
没有飞机的过度帮助
561
00:29:01,833 --> 00:29:02,733
at depth
在深处
562
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,066
bow planes are now used to alter the ship's depth
船首平面现在被用来改变船的深度
563
00:29:07,333 --> 00:29:09,333
doors individual
门个体
564
00:29:09,333 --> 00:29:10,600
watertight compartments
水密舱
565
00:29:10,600 --> 00:29:13,266
can serve to isolate damaged areas of the hull
可以用来隔离船体的受损区域
566
00:29:13,533 --> 00:29:15,066
so the ship can remain afloat
这样船才能保持漂浮
567
00:29:15,066 --> 00:29:17,100
even if one section is flooded
即使有一段被淹了
568
00:29:18,266 --> 00:29:20,066
as such special doors
就像这样的特殊门
569
00:29:20,066 --> 00:29:23,000
are designed to withstand high pressure conditions
设计用于承受高压条件
570
00:29:25,066 --> 00:29:27,866
they're installed into the reinforced bulkheads
它们被安装在加固的舱壁上
571
00:29:31,066 --> 00:29:31,733
there are sturdy
有坚固的
572
00:29:31,733 --> 00:29:35,300
rotating levers at the edges of the door called dogs
门边缘的旋转杠杆叫做狗
573
00:29:39,233 --> 00:29:41,666
with a couple turns of a central handle
有几个中央手柄
574
00:29:42,300 --> 00:29:46,466
a worm gear actuates parts connected to individual dogs
蜗轮驱动连接到单个狗的零件
575
00:29:51,133 --> 00:29:53,433
rotating these levers into place
将这些杠杆旋转到位
576
00:29:56,533 --> 00:29:58,433
the inherent leverage in the system
系统中的固有杠杆
577
00:29:58,433 --> 00:30:00,033
makes for a tight seal
使密封紧密
578
00:30:04,833 --> 00:30:06,433
as the rubber door gasket
作为橡胶门垫圈
579
00:30:08,033 --> 00:30:11,200
presses against an exposed metal part of the door frame
按压门框外露的金属部分
580
00:30:11,333 --> 00:30:12,733
called the knife edge
叫做刀刃
581
00:30:16,466 --> 00:30:19,900
these submarines are sea going works of art
这些潜艇是海上艺术品
582
00:30:20,266 --> 00:30:22,400
and even with the detail I've shown
即使我展示了这些细节
583
00:30:22,500 --> 00:30:25,200
there's so much more to them than I could cover here
他们比我在这里描述的要多得多
584
00:30:25,233 --> 00:30:26,066
I'm in awe
我很敬畏
585
00:30:26,066 --> 00:30:28,700
of the skilled folks who built these machines
制造这些机器的技术人员
